  h3 Ingredients
  div.ingredients
    ul
        li 2 tbsp cooking oil
        li 1/2 yellow onion, roughly chopped
        li 3 large garlic cloves, minced
        li 1 inch piece of ginger, minced
        li 1 small red chilli, finely chopped
        li 1 tsp ground cumin
        li 1 tsp ground coriander 
        li 1 tsp ground turmeric
        li 1/2 tsp ground cinnamon
        li 3 tbsp medium curry powder/curry paste
        li 1 tsp smoked paprika
        li 1/2 tbsp dried curry leaves
        li Juice from 1/2 medium-sized lime
        li 2 potatoes, roughly chopped
        li 1 can chopped tomatoes (400g)
        li 200 ml coconut cream
        li 1 cup red lentils
        li Fresh coriander (cilantro) for garnish
        li 2 cups cooked  basmati rice, to serve
        li Freshly baked flatbreads, to serve

  h3 Preparation Directions 
  div.steps
    ul 
        li Heat oil in a medium-sized saucepan. 
        li Add the onion, garlic, chilli, ginger and all the spices and curry leaves.
        li Fry until fragrant, 2-3 minutes. 
        li Add the potatoes and fry for 3 more minutes, until slightly golden.
        li Add the coconut milk, chopped tomatoes, water and lentils and bring to a simmer.
        li Let simmer for 30 minutes, until the potatoes and lentils are soft.
        li Season with salt, pepper and lime juice. 
        li Serve over cooked rice with flatbreads and garnish with fresh coriander.